<collectingRegion box="[1125,1246,1426,1455]" country="Malawi" name="Kasungu" pageId="41" pageNumber="99">Kasungu</collectingRegion>
N.P [= Nanional Park],” 
<collectingCountry box="[1011,1111,1466,1495]" name="Malawi" pageId="41" pageNumber="99">Malawi</collectingCountry>
.
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="41.[731,1325,1342,1770]" pageId="41" pageNumber="99">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bergmans &amp; van Strien" authorityYear="2004" box="[731,994,1501,1534]" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Epomophorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="99" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="anselli">Epomophorus anselli</taxonomicName>
is in the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Ogilby" baseAuthorityYear="1835" box="[1122,1263,1501,1534]" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Epomophorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="99" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gambianus">gambianus</taxonomicName>
species group and is known with certainty from only three specimens. Measurements overlap with large northern 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Temminck" authorityYear="1837" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Epomophorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="99" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="labiatus">E. labiatus</taxonomicName>
