</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[114,944,2762,2795]" pageId="41" pageNumber="99" type="activity">
<paragraph blockId="41.[114,1323,1776,2994]" box="[114,944,2762,2795]" pageId="41" pageNumber="99">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[114,349,2762,2795]" pageId="41" pageNumber="99">Activity patterns.</emphasis>
Ansell’s Epauletted Fruit Bat is nocturnal.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[115,1055,2806,2835]" pageId="41" pageNumber="99" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="41.[114,1323,1776,2994]" box="[115,1055,2806,2835]" pageId="41" pageNumber="99">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[115,816,2806,2835]" pageId="41" pageNumber="99">Movements, Home range and Social organization.</emphasis>
No information.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="41" pageNumber="99" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="41.[114,1323,1776,2994]" pageId="41" pageNumber="99">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[115,471,2842,2875]" pageId="41" pageNumber="99">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Data Deficient on The IUCN Red List. Ansell’s Epauletted Fruit Bat was recently described, and there is a lack of information on its distribution,status, threats, and ecological requirements.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
